CAPE TOWN - The bloodbath in the Western Cape's taxi industry appears to be out of control. Since last year, 116 people have died in taxi-related violence. Taxi operators say they are living in fear. WATCH: 'Gauteng taxi bosses law unto themselves' Western Cape Transport MEC Bonginkosi Madikizela says efforts have been made by provincial government to resolve the feuds between rival taxi associations but says the taxi industry has a tendency not to obey the law. Mini-bus taxi owners are part of a multi-billion Rand industry in South Africa and the recent killings in the Western Cape show just how far some are willing to go to take out competitors for a piece of the lucrative pie. eNCA's Ronald Masinda has the story.